File: Minister of Transport Fikile Mbalula.  JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says there will be amendments to long-distance travel. He says this will apply to people travelling under exceptional circumstances. READ: Gautrain back on track Mbalula says he has been in communication with Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma and Police Minister Bheki Cele on determining long-distance travel regulations. "So that by today before the end of the day we gazette the direction that will enable long-distance travel particularly public transport for people to be catered for in terms of long-distance travelling," Mbalula said. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.